snippet: Congress has not asked for a vote to approve military action in Iraq aimed at ISIS militants, and President Obama is not seeking one.
abstract: Both Pres Obama and members of Congress appear reluctant to carry out vote on military action in Iraq; Obama's hesitation reflects marked change in attitude from his push for action in Syria in 2013, effort that yielded little support in Congress.
lead_paragraph: Congress has not asked for a vote to approve military action in Iraq aimed at ISIS militants, and President Obama is not seeking one.

headline.main: Neither Obama Nor Congress Seems Eager for a Vote on Military Action in Iraq
